{
  "text": "Control Cr Metal-lymphocyte transformation tests. None of the ARMD samples showed increased lymphocyte reactivity to Cr or Co in vitro, or demonstrated an elevated incidence of metal sensitivity above that of the general population (10% to 15%). [CITATION_1] Only one ARMD patient showed metal reactivity, which was a mild response to aluminium, molybdenum and nickel (Table V) .",
